Levrat Seeks Swiss Proprietary Trading Ban, SonntagsZeitung Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-10-16T12:29:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/levrat-seeks-swiss-proprietary-trading-ban-sonntagszeitung-says.html
Christian Levrat, head of
Switzerland’s Social Democratic Party, said he will propose
legislation to ban proprietary trading at the country’s largest
banks, including  UBS AG (UBSN)  and  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) ,
 SonntagsZeitung  reported, citing an interview.  Levrat said the lenders should reduce their investment-
banking operations to a minimum, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in Frankfurt at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  